  <TITLE>Set env vars on `drone exec --local`</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>This is a feature request based on the thread here: &gt; https://discourse.drone.io/t/set-env-vars-on-drone-exec-local/1689 In summary, I'm requesting that both the `-e`/`--env` &amp; `--env-file` flags be added to Drone, in a way analogous to Docker's usage of these flags. The environment variables defined by these flags should be populated into the environment of all build steps in a pipeline when run via `drone exec --local`. With a slight bit of guidance (pointer to key files &amp; branch to start from) I'd be happy to give implementing this a go.</DESCRIPTION>
